Telkom South Africa’s Operating Revenue Declines by 5.2% For the Full Year

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-06-13T05:06:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/telkom-south-africa-s-operating-revenue-declines-by-5-2-for-the-full-year.html
Telkom South Africa Ltd., the
continent’s largest fixed-line operator, said normalised
operating revenue for the 12 months to March 31 declined by 5.2
percent to 33.4 billion rand.  Telkom commented in a stock exchange statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  